2025-09-29 11:25:55,284 - INFO - Strategy Summary: The data showed that slower aspirate and dispense speeds, as well as longer aspirate and dispense wait times, tend to result in lower deviation and variability, suggesting more accurate and precise pipetting. However, these parameters also increase the time taken for the procedure, indicating a trade-off between accuracy/precision and efficiency. Therefore, parameters should be chosen to balance these factors. The recommended parameters aim to achieve this balance.
2025-09-29 11:25:55,286 - INFO - LLM Recommendation 1:
2025-09-29 11:25:55,286 - INFO -   Confidence Level: medium
2025-09-29 11:25:55,286 - INFO -   Reasoning: The experiment with the lowest deviation and variability had aspirate and dispense speeds of 16 and 30, respectively, and aspirate and dispense wait times of 4.259607 and 27.094172, respectively. The proposed parameters are chosen as an average of the observed best performing parameters. The overaspirate_vol is chosen as an average of the observed values and the air volumes are set to the mid-range values.
